<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">daṇḍānata narēndrēṇa</hi>
<lb n="2"/><hi rend="grantha">narēndrēṇaiṣa kārita<unclear>m</unclear></hi>
<lb n="3"/><hi rend="grantha">śatṛūmallēna śailmēsmin</hi>
<lb n="4"/><hi rend="grantha">śatramallēśvarālayaḥ</hi>
</p>

<p>Two late inscriptions below this record the names of a God and Goddess.</p>

<p>A</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/><seg xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">pañcavanaṉ</seg>
<lb n="2" break="no"/><hi rend="grantha">dhi</hi><seg xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">curaṉ</seg>
</p>

<p>B</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/><seg xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">periya n<unclear>ā</unclear>c</seg>
<lb n="2" break="no"/><seg xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">ciyammai</seg>
